	"description": "An overview of different app design options\nWhen we design software, we constantly think about error cases. Errors have a\nhuge impact on the way we design and architecture a solution. So much so, in\nfact, that there is a philosophy known as Let It Crash\n[http://wiki.c2.com/?LetItCrash].\n\nLet it crash is the Erlang way to treat failures by just letting the application\ncrash and allowing a supervisor to restart the crashed process from a clean\nstate.\n\nSupervisors restart the crashed processErrors ",
